         <abstract>
            <p>Return on investment may have its uses--for assessing prospective investments or disinvestments, for example. But when judging companies, product lines, facilities or executive performance, return on investment--whether it's based on total assets, investment, equity or any other over-the-hill number--is not a reliable guide.</p>
